Attribution
- All wireframe design, UI structure, and API integration written by me
- Code snippets referenced from GeeksforGeeks and Claude AI (Anthropic) for utility logic, patterns, and as reference sources for external library use
- UI polish and refinement and refactors assisted by Claude AI tool
- Additional packages (helmet, express-rate-limit) added to the backend for security improvements
- All packages are listed in package.json and installed via npm install

Prerequisites
- Node.js 22+
- npm (comes with Node.js)

Backend Setup
1. cd backend
2. npm install
3. npx prisma generate
4. npx prisma db push
5. npx prisma db seed
6. node --watch src/server.js 3000

Frontend Setup
1. cd frontend
2. npm install
3. npm run dev (development, runs on port 5173)
4. npm run build (production, outputs to frontend/dist)

Deployment
- Hosted on Railway using Docker (see Dockerfile and railway.json)
- Railway builds the Docker image, which installs dependencies, builds the frontend, and starts the backend
- The backend serves the built frontend static files, the API, and Socket.IO on a single port
- Railway sets the PORT environment variable automatically

Environment
- Backend uses SQLite 
- Backend serves uploaded files from its own /uploads directory
- Set JWT_SECRET environment variable for production